p: All samples were confirmed as HIV-1 positive. In total, 78% (67/84) of the samples were successfully amplified and sequenced. The median age among the 84 individuals was 22 years (IQR: 20–23) and 83% were females, which was similar to the age (22 years [IQR: 20–24]) and gender distribution (87% females) of the 67 participants whose samples were successfully genotyped (p = 0.992 and p = 0.653, M-W and Fisher exact test, respectively).
